Jeremy Bernard has been named as the Special Assistant to the President and Social Secretary. He joins the White House staff from the U.S. Embassy in Paris, where he serves as Senior Advisor to the Ambassador. Previously, he worked as the White House Liaison to the National Endowment for the Humanities. Jeremy shares the vision for the White House as the People's House, one that celebrates history and culture in dynamic and inclusive ways. He will continue to showcase America's arts and culture through various events at the White House. Jeremy's work at the National Endowment for the Humanities was praised for his humor, good will, and professionalism. He has a background in finance and served as a board member for various organizations focused on equality and LGBT rights.